    howToUse: "Wear faience jewelry for protection, particularly pieces shaped as traditional Egyptian symbols. Display faience figurines in a home as protective objects. Gift faience-style jewelry or reproductions to those interested in Egyptian spiritual tradition. Meditate with a faience piece to connect with ancient Egyptian protective practice.",
    funFact: "In 2009, researchers at the British Museum discovered that ancient Egyptian blue faience has a unique property: it fluoresces (glows) under ultraviolet light, emitting visible near-infrared radiation. This luminescent quality — invisible to the naked eye in ordinary light — may have contributed to the ancient Egyptians' belief in faience's supernatural properties, as they may have observed this glow in certain lighting conditions.",
